      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "body": "1 ½ pounds Flank Steak.",
          "tone": "info",
          "title": "Also"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cut flank steak into thin strips. In a ziplock bag add flank steak pieces and cornstarch. Shake to coat.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add sesame oil, minced garlic, soy sauce, beef broth, brown sugar, onion, and red pepper flakes to the slow cooker. Stir ingredients.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add coated flank steak and stir again until coated in the sauce.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cook for high 2-3 hours or on low 4-5 hours until cooked throughout and tender. Can serve over rice and garnish with green onions.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Switch to low and shorter, or pick a fattier cut (shoulder, shin, chuck). Eight hours on low is the safe sweet spot for most cuts.",
              "cause": "Cooked on high too long, or the cut was too lean.",
              "symptom": "Meat is stringy or dry"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Lift the lid for the last 30 minutes on high, or transfer the sauce to a saucepan and reduce on the hob.",
              "cause": "Slow cookers don't evaporate, every drop of liquid stays in.",
              "symptom": "Sauce is watery"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Add anything that cooks in under 20 minutes in the last half-hour. Root veg can go in from the beginning.",
              "cause": "Soft veg (courgette, peas, leafy greens) added at the start.",
              "symptom": "Vegetables are mush"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Brown meat in a pan first, five minutes a side. The fond at the bottom of the pan goes in too. Worth the extra washing-up.",
              "cause": "Meat went in raw without browning.",
              "symptom": "Lacks depth"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Hob version: brown the meat, then transfer to a casserole dish in a 150°C oven for the same length of time, 3 to 4 hours.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Vegetarian: replace meat with 600 g mixed root veg and 200 g lentils; cut cooking time by a third.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The slow cooker is the make-ahead.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Chinese home cooking favours bright contrast: salt, sweet, sour, heat, working against each other in one bowl. The dish lands somewhere on that grid, adjust the balance to suit your palate.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
